<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,546,2011]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1554,1579]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Distribution.</emphasis>
Only the 
<typeStatus box="[467,568,1554,1579]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">holotype</typeStatus>
, collected near the mouth of the Rio Amazonas (
<figureCitation box="[1125,1208,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1507,1529]" captionTargetBox="[270,1319,200,1477]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[262,1325,193,1485]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 21. Geographic distribution map for the new species of Paravelia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285802/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[1179,1208,1555,1579]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
) is known up to the present. It is the only species of 
<taxonomicName box="[511,621,1590,1614]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Paravelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[511,621,1590,1614]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Paravelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recorded from the Amapá State.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1250,1626,1651]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,546,2011]" box="[199,1250,1626,1651]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1626,1651]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after the Amapá State, northern 
<collectingCountry box="[787,858,1626,1651]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, where the 
<typeStatus box="[986,1084,1626,1651]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
